\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 3. G. punctata} Lapeyr., {\i Hist. Abr. Pyr.} 57 (1813) ({\i G. aphyllanthes} auct., non Crantz,{\i  G. willkommii} Nyman). Stolons absent; stems up to 30 cm. Lower leaves forming a rosette, obovate to spathulate, rounded or weakly emarginate, petiolate; lateral veins clearly visible above; cauline leaves lanceolate to oblong, sessile. Capitula c. 1·5 cm in diameter; involucral bracts numerous, lanceolate, acuminate. Calyx-teeth about as long as tube, linear-lanceolate. 2n = 16. {\i From N. France and Czechoslovakia southwards to N. Spain, S. Italy and N.E. Greece; S.C. & E. Russia.} Au Be Bu Cz Ga Ge Gr He Hs Hu It Ju Rm Rs (C, E) Tu.
